   "hider_text": "The light here moves differently—slanted, like a slow breath across the floor. It pools in the corner where the wall meets the wooden shelf, and for a moment, it looks like something that’s been waiting to be seen. There’s a scent—old paper and salt, not quite real, like the memory of wind through a window after rain.  \n\nThe floor creaks under the",
